<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Palette tools?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=9613&amp;p=104758#p104758"><![CDATA[
Or in GIMP: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Create a new RGB image of the same size. </li><li>Fill it with the first color in the desired palette. </li><li>Image &gt; Mode &gt; Indexed and accept the defaults. </li><li>Open the colormap: Windows &gt; Dockable Dialogs &gt; Colormap. </li><li>For each color in order, choose the color in the color picker, then add it to the new image's colormap. </li><li>Paste something into this window. </li></ol><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Dec 15, 2012 3:24 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
